      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 99,
      "message": "For \"F\", I'm thinking this is sufficient.  However, even for \"G\", I'm not sure we want to load anything, if the DB is already populated.  If the user wants to add policies/types to an existing DB, that should be done via curl, not by changing the config and bouncing the process.\n\nChecking policy type should be sufficient; if the DB contains a policy, then it must also contain the associated policy type, while the converse is not necessarily true.",
